ğŸŒ DORA Process (DHCP ka funda)

âš¡ Full form â†’ Discover â€“ Offer â€“ Request â€“ Acknowledge
ğŸ‘‰ Ye ek 4 step process hai jo hota hai jab koi device (PC, mobile, laptop, router) network pe aata hai aur IP address khud se maangta hai DHCP server se.

ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Discover (D)

        Jab ek new device network pe connect hota hai (jaise Wi-Fi join karta hai), uske paas abhi koi IP address nahi hota.
        
        Wo ek broadcast message bhejta hai â†’ "Koi DHCP server hai kya? Mujhe ek IP chahiye!"

ğŸ‘‰ Real Life Example (Hindi):
        Soch tu ek hotel me aaya hai bina room book kiye. Tu reception pe jaake bolta hai:
        "Hello! Koi room khaali hai kya? Mujhe ek room chahiye."

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Offer (O)

        Jo DHCP Server hota hai wo sunta hai aur reply karta hai â†’ "Haan mere paas IP address hai. Tu 192.168.1.10 use kar sakta hai. Saath me subnet mask, gateway, DNS bhi de raha hu."
        
        Ye ek offer hoti hai, matlab ek suggestion.

ğŸ‘‰ Hotel Example:
        Receptionist bolta hai:
        "Yes, ek room khaali hai. Tu Room No. 101 le sakta hai."

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Request (R)

        Ab client (device) confirm karta hai aur bolta hai â†’ "Ok mujhe ye 192.168.1.10 wali IP chahiye. Please ye reserve kar do sirf mere liye."
        
        Ye ek request hoti hai.

ğŸ‘‰ Hotel Example:
        Tu receptionist ko bolta hai:
        "Ok mujhe Room No. 101 pasand hai. Main wahi lunga. Dusre guest ko mat dena."

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Acknowledge (A)

        Ab DHCP Server officially confirm karta hai aur bolta hai â†’ "Theek hai, ab se 192.168.1.10 teri IP hai. Ab isse use kar."
        
        Iske saath hi client ko Subnet Mask, Default Gateway, DNS Server ka data bhi milta hai.

ğŸ‘‰ Hotel Example:
        Receptionist bolta hai:
        "Theek hai sir. Room No. 101 ab officially aapka hai. Ye keys le lijiye."

âœ… Final Result

      Device ke paas proper IP configuration aa jata hai:
      
      IP Address
      
      Subnet Mask
      
      Default Gateway
      
      DNS Server

Ab wo network pe dusre devices aur Internet ke sath baat kar sakta hai.

ğŸ”‘ Shortcut Formula (yaad rakhne ka easy way)

        D â†’ Discover = "Koi hai mujhe IP dene wala?"
        
        O â†’ Offer = "Haan, ye IP le sakta hai."
        
        R â†’ Request = "Mujhe ye IP chahiye."
        
        A â†’ Acknowledge = "Ok, ye IP ab teri hai."

ğŸ‘‰ Matlab DORA = ek hotel me room allotment jaisa hai.

      IP = Room Number
      
      DHCP Server = Receptionist
      
      Client = Guest (Tu)
